column1: Kevin Gauthier assisted in data collection

column2: Windy. very clear. Started raining at start of survey- but quit after a few minutes.

44 feet at deep hole. 2 points on GPS labeled as Franklin deep hole - SWDV was used to find true Deep Hole point. The difference in depth was 44 ft vs 20 ft. Very windy- sunny- clear skies- warm - but we had been relatively cold the last few days.
Cloudy- overcast but not raining. A boat of 4 people fishing on the lake other than us. A loon and her chick were spotted near the survey boat.
